040%25%20of%20GitHub's%20growth.%3Cp%3EAssociated%20Press%2FDita%20Alangkara%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGitHub%20is%2C%20fundamentally%2C%20a%20hosting%20platform%20for%20coders.%20The%20cloud-based%20service%20allows%20coders%20to%20effectively%20manage%20and%20maintain%20open-source%20programming%20projects%20while%20collaborating%20with%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20how%20GitHub%20works%2C%20you%20have%20to%20have%20an%20understanding%20of%20%26quot%3BGit%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20idea%20of%20%26quot%3Bversion%20control%26quot%3B%20in%20relation%20to%20Git.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGit%2C%20started%20by%20Linux%20creator%20Linus%20Torvalds%2C%20is%20an%20open-source%20version%20control%20system%20that%20tracks%20changes%20in%20files%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVersion%20control%20is%20an%20important%20system%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20coding.%20It%20enables%20coders%20to%20be%20nimble%20with%20programming%2C%20and%20allows%20for%20apps%20to%20constantly%20have%20new%20version%20releases%2C%20expansion%20to%20other%20platforms%2C%20and%20bug%20fixes%2C%20among%20other%20tracked%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVersion%20control%20systems%20like%20Git%20help%20maintain%20the%20integrity%20and%20security%20of%20ever-evolving%20code%20by%20safeguarding%20modifications%2C%20and%20those%20revisions%20are%20then%20hosted%20by%20GitHub%2C%20or%20an%20alternative%20%26quot%3Brepository%26quot%3B%20hosting%20service%20%E2%80%94%20although%20GitHub%20is%20the%20most%20popular%20among%20developers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20allows%20developers%20to%20easily%20collaborate%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20download%20a%20new%20version%20of%20the%20software%2C%20make%20changes%2C%20and%20upload%20the%20newest%20revision.%20Every%20developer%20can%20see%20these%20new%20changes%2C%20download%20them%2C%20and%20contribute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247df62dc-bd53-43fb-8b7e-cf67a2322e19%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdvantages%20of%20GitHub%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20sites%20that%20feature%20Git%20repositories%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20the%20term%20used%20for%20where%20Git%20is%20stored%2C%20often%20shortened%20to%20%26quot%3Brepo%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20GitHub%20is%20the%20most%20popular%2C%20and%20thus%2C%20has%20the%20most%20to%20offer%20collaboratively.%20Put%20simply%2C%20it's%20the%20standard%20for%20coders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20several%20features%20that%20have%20made%20GitHub%20so%20popular%20with%20developers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EForking%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20GitHub%20makes%20it%20easy%20to%20forge%20your%20own%20coding%20project%20based%20on%20an%20existing%20one%20hosted%20on%20GitHub.%20With%20%26quot%3Bforking%2C%26quot%3B%20you%20can%20easily%20take%20the%20blueprint%20of%20a%20project%20and%20fork%20it%20off%20in%20a%20different%2C%20more%20applicable%20direction%20for%20your%20own%20use%2C%20without%20affecting%20the%20original%20repository.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPull%20requests%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20GitHub%20also%20offers%20support%20to%20coders%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%26quot%3Bpull%20requests.%26quot%3B%20Say%20you've%20forked%20a%20repo%20and%20want%20recognition%20for%20your%20efforts.%20You%20can%20communicate%20that%20to%20the%20original%20authors%20of%20the%20repo%20via%20GitHub's%20pull%20request%20feature.%20Those%20creators%20will%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20inspect%20your%20work%20and%20decide%20if%20they%20want%20to%20include%20your%20fork%20in%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20original%20project.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESocial%20networking%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20collaborative%20aspects%20of%20GitHub%20make%20it%20more%20than%20a%20hosting%20service%2C%20but%20also%20a%20social%20networking%20site%2C%20complete%20with%20user%20profiles%20and%20a%20history%20of%20user%20contributions%20in%20the%20form%20of%20pull%20requests.%20Projects%20are%20also%20discussed%20publicly%20as%20they're%20revised%2C%20making%20it%20easy%20to%20quickly%20crowdsource%20any%20needed%20coding%20expertise.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBranching%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20When%20collaborating%2C%20GitHub%20allows%20%26quot%3Bbranching%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20a%20repository%20can%20be%20duplicated%20and%20changed%20by%20another%20collaborator%20without%20affecting%20the%20original%20code.%20Once%20tested%2C%20the%20new%20code%20can%20then%20be%20merged%20and%20incorporated%20into%20the%20original.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EChangelogs%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20GitHub%20also%20keeps%20changelogs%20that%20tracks%20a%20project's%20changes%20and%20who%20made%20them%20%E2%80%94%20crucial%20for%20good%20collaboration%20among%20multiple%20programmers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20disadvantages%20to%20Github%2C%20too.%20GitHub%20users%20have%20been%20vocal%20in%20the%20past%20about%20complaints%20with%20the%20platform%3B%20some%20say%20GitHub%20is%20expensive%2C%20buggy%2C%20and%20insufficient%20for%20large%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22463af26d-e956-4e25-a027-a1d597446cf8%5C%22%3EIs%20GitHub%20free%20to%20use%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGitHub%20has%20a%20free%20version%20with%20limited%20bandwidth%20and%20storage%2C%20and%20two%20paid%20versions.%20The%20Team%20subscription%20is%20geared%20towards%20individuals%20and%20organizations%20seeking%20%26quot%3Badvanced%20collaboration%26quot%3B%20options%2C%20and%20costs%20%244%20per%20user%20per%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Enterprise%20subscription%20costs%20%2421%20per%20user%20per%20month%2C%20and%20has%20the%20same%20advantages%20as%20Team%2C%20plus%20a%20host%20of%20other%20advanced%20features%2C%20greater%20security%2C%20and%20premium%20support%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d0a33ed1-df73-4355-82eb-356af6609c24%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20start%20using%20Github%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20looking%20for%20a%20resource%20to%20maintain%20and%20share%20code%2C%20you%20can%20easily%20install%20Git%20and%20sig