r.com%2F67855d488951662c9f1fe3fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Meyssonnier%2FAP%20Images%3B%20Lindsey%20Nicholson%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAlmost%2050%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20young%20Donald%20Trump%20had%20a%20career%20breakthrough%20redeveloping%20a%20NYC%20hotel.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20developers%20want%20to%20replace%20the%20property%20with%20the%20country's%20most%20expensive%20tower.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20project's%20builders%20need%20almost%20%245%20billion%20of%20federal%20loans%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%20was%20a%20young%20developer%20eager%20to%20make%20a%20name%20for%20himself%20in%20the%20Manhattan%20real%20estate%20industry%20when%20he%20struck%20a%20career-making%20deal%20to%20redevelop%20the%20Commodore%20Hotel%20next%20to%20Grand%20Central%20Terminal%20into%20a%201%2C300-room%20Grand%20Hyatt%20clad%20in%20dark%20glass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20half%20a%20century%20later%2C%20Trump%20may%20again%20have%20an%20opportunity%20to%20play%20a%20role%20in%20the%20site's%20destiny%20when%20he%20returns%20to%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20developers%20RXR%20and%20TF%20Cornerstone%20have%20proposed%20leveling%20the%20property%20and%20raising%20a%201%2C575-foot-tall%20office%20and%20hotel%20tower%20in%20its%20place%20that%20would%20cost%20as%20much%20as%20%246.5%20billion%20to%20construct.%20It%20would%20be%20both%20the%20tallest%20skyscraper%20by%20roof%20height%20ever%20built%20in%20America%20as%20well%20as%20the%20most%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERenderings%20of%20the%20mega-tower%20show%20how%20it%20will%20dwarf%20surrounding%20structures%2C%20including%20the%20neighboring%20landmark%20Chrysler%20Building%20and%20even%20a%20new%20headquarters%20tower%20being%20built%20nearby%20for%20JPMorgan%20Chase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20work%2C%20the%20pair%20have%20imagined%20making%20improvements%20to%20portions%20of%20the%20historic%20neighboring%20train%20terminal%20and%20the%20subway%20station%20below%20the%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20rendering%20of%20a%20proposed%20skyscraper%20near%20the%20Chrysler%20Building%20in%20Midtown%20Manhattan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67857f2be294a7514e8cd85e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223640%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E175%20Park%2C%20center%2C%20would%20tower%20over%20neighboring%20skyscrapers%2C%20including%20the%20Chrysler%20Building.%3Cp%3ERXR%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20pay%20for%20the%20immense%20project%20%E2%80%94%20called%20175%20Park%20Avenue%20%E2%80%94%20the%20developers%20are%20taking%20an%20unusual%20approach%20at%20a%20moment%20when%20lenders%20have%20remained%20wary%20to%20finance%20such%20large-scale%20office%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20property%20was%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transportation.gov%2Fsites%2Fbuildamerica.dot.gov%2Ffiles%2F2024-12%2FWeb%2520LOI%2520List.Dec%25202024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluded%20on%20a%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20mostly%20transportation%20related%20projects%20that%20are%20seeking%20access%20to%20federal%20money%20earmarked%20for%20transit%20infrastructure%20development%20and%20upgrades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERXR%20and%20TF%20Cornerstone%20are%20planning%20to%20apply%20for%20as%20much%20as%20%244.84%20billion%20of%20federal%20loans%20to%20help%20pay%20for%20the%20tower%2C%20according%20to%20the%20document.%20The%20developers%20expect%20to%20spend%20as%20much%20as%20%246.5%20billion%20on%20the%20project%2C%20a%20sum%20that%20includes%20about%20%24550%20million%20of%20accompanying%20transit%20improvements%20they%20will%20make%20as%20part%20of%20the%20project.%20The%20team%20is%20listed%20as%20having%20submitted%20a%20draft%20letter%20of%20interest%20in%20the%20federal%20money%2C%20a%20preliminary%20and%20non-binding%20step%20in%20applying%20for%20the%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20money%20is%20discretionary%20and%20administered%20by%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Transportation%2C%20meaning%20that%20the%20incoming%20Trump%20administration%20%E2%80%94%20and%20possibly%20even%20the%20president%20himself%20%E2%80%94%20will%20have%20decision-making%20authority%20over%20which%20projects%20are%20ultimately%20awarded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20expect%20he'd%20be%20supportive%20and%20excited%20about%20it%2C%20and%20obviously%20at%20the%20appropriate%20time%20we're%20going%20to%20be%20reaching%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20Rechler%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20chairman%20of%20RXR%2C%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20he%20hadn't%20yet%20attempted%20to%20discuss%20the%20tower%20project%20with%20the%20president-elect%20or%20anyone%20in%20his%20circle.%20%26quot%3BHe%20understands%20office%20buildings%20better%20than%20any%20president%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2214042eb0-2043-429b-a4f2-e9093889762e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20shortage%20of%20capital%20for%20office%20development%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERechler%20said%20the%20project%20team%20behind%20175%20Park%20Avenue%20is%20exploring%20the%20federal%20loans%20because%20of%20lingering%20dislocations%20in%20the%20lending%20market%20that%20have%20made%20it%20difficult%20to%20source%20financing%20from%20private%20sector%20lenders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBanks%2C%20life%20insurance%20companies%2C%20debt%20funds%2C%20and%20other%20sources%20of%20mortgage%20debt%20have%20pulled%20away%20from%20office%20financing%20as%20a%20result%20of%20concerns%20about%20the%20stresses%20of%20higher%20interest%20rates%20on%20property%20values%20and%20vacancies%20created%20by%20the%20enduring%20popularity%20of%20hybrid%20and%20remote%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrey%20Morsbach%2C%20an%20executive%20managing%20director%20at%20JLL%20who%20co-leads%20the%20firm's%20real%20estate%20debt%20advisory%20practice%2C%20said%20that%20multi-billion-dollar%20office%20projects%20are%20tricky%20to%20finance%20even%20during%20favorable%20leasing%20and%20lending%20conditions%2C%20requiring%20collections%20of%20lenders%20to%20divide%20the%20loan%20and%20spread%20their%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Vanderbilt%2C%20a%20roughly%201%2C400-foot-tall%20tower%20that%20opened%20in%202020%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20Grand%20Central%20Terminal%20from%20175%20Park%20Avenue%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fslgreen.com%2Fsl-green-closes-1-5-billion-construction-financing-paving-way-for-one-vanderbilt-development%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceived%20a%20%241.5%20billion%20construction%20loan%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20group%20of%20six%20banks%20in%202016%20in%20order%20to%20proceed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorsbach%20said%20that%20lenders%20were%20still%20funding%20office%20construction%20today%2C%20in%20large%20part%20because%20there%20is%20a%20growing%20belief%20that%20newly%20built%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foffice-construction-demand-upcoming-shortage-real-estate-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-end%20spaces%20will%20outperform%20the%20broader%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20pool%20of%20active%20financing%20groups%20has%20shrunk%2C%20however%2C%20challenging%20deals%20like%20175%20Park%20Avenue%20that%20rely%20on%20lending%20consortiums%20and%20benefit%20from%20market%20depth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELenders%20%26quot%3Bare%20interested%2C%20but%20just%20aren't%20willing%20to%20commit%20the%20same%20scale%2C%26quot%3B%20Morsbach%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227c98ab0d-5aec-4b5d-8100-71a54211a3f0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20unused%20pot%20of%20tens%20of%20billions%20of%20federal%20dollars%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERXR%20and%20TF%20Cornerstone%20are%20aiming%20to%20tap%20lending%20programs%20called%20the%20Transportation%20Infrastructure%20Finance%20and%20Innovation%20Act%20and%20Railroad%20Rehabilitation%20and%20Improvement%20Financing.%20The%20programs%2C%20known%20by%20their%20acronyms%20Tifia%20and%20Rrif%2C%20respectively%2C%20offer%20projects%20access%20to%20low-cost%20financing%20and%20long%20payback%20periods%20stretching%2035%20years%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20benefits%20of%20sourcing%20a%20loan%20at%20the%20scale%20necessary%20to%20fund%20the%20construction%20of%20175%20Park%20Avenue%20from%20the%20federal%20government%20versus%20the%20private%20market%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%20astronomical%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20developers%2C%20according%20to%20Stijn%20Van%20Nieuwerburgh%2C%20the%20Earle%20W.%20Kazis%20and%20Benjamin%20Schore%20Professor%20of%20Real%20Estate%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20programs%20are%20aimed%20at%20transit%20upgrades%2C%20they%20were%20updated%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Infrastructure%20Investment%20and%20Jobs%20Act%20in%202021%20to%20allow%20funding%20for%20private%20development%20located%20%26quot%3Bwithin%20a%20half%20mile%20walking%20distance%20of%20transit%20%E2%80%94%20commuter%20and%20intercity%20passenger%20rail%20stations%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20DOT%20spokeswoman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFew%20builders%2C%20however%2C%20have%20tapped%20the%20money%2C%20even%20though%20the%20Rrif%20program%20holds%20about%20%2430%20billion%20of%20unused%20funds%2C%20in%20part%2C%20because%20of%20the%20tedious%20qualification%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20receive%20the%20financing%2C%20the%20175%20Park%20Avenue%20project%20must%20receive%20an%20investment%20grade%20credit%20rating%20from%20a%20major%20ratings%20agency%20and%20pass%20through%20a%20federal%20environmental%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20extremely%20cumbersome%20to%20access%20that%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Van%20Nieuwerburgh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225320%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Scott%20Rechler%2C%20center%2C%20in%20a%20group%20of%20men%20in%20hard%20hats%20and%20lime-green%20jackets%20and%20vests.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67817f9288b000981b4a75f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223568%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EScott%20Rechler%2C%20second%20from%20right%3Cp%3EMark%20Lennihan%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommercial-real-estate-office-interest-rates-risks-industrial-trump-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoptimism%20in%20the%20commercial%20real%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%20industry%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20will%20be%20more%20accommodative%20of%20business%2C%20including%20by%20stripping%20back%20regulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDonald%20Trump%20comes%20in%2C%20his%20team%20cuts%20through%20the%20red%20tape%2C%20navigates%20through%20and%20unleashes%20a%20%246%20billion%20project%20that's%20going%20to%20improve%20transit%2C%20create%20the%20biggest%20building%20in%20the%20Western%20hemisphere%2C%26quot%3B%20Rechler%20said%20of%20175%20Park%20Avenue's%20potential%20appeal%20to%20the%20president-elect.%20%26quot%3BIt%20speaks%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20his%20policies%20and%20the%20administration's%20approach%20to%20wanting%20to%20get%20things%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cd91a24e-6e9b-460b-a219-f854bdab24ec%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnflattering%20politics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERechler%2C%20however%2C%20was%20for%20years%20closely%20aligned%20politically%20with%20former%20New%20York%20Governor%20Andrew%20Cuomo%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Democrat%20and%20nemesis%20of%20Trump's%20during%20his%20first%20term%20in%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERechler%2C%20who%20noted%20he%20is%20a%20registered%20independent%2C%20is%20hoping%20that%20economic%20development%20will%20prevail%20over%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20person%20who%20is%20in%20line%20to%20become%20a%20Trump%20administration%20official%20said%20that%20Rechler's%20past%20associations%20may%20not%20be%20lost%20on%20the%20new%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20speaking%20for%20Trump%2C%20but%20I%20would%20be%20in%20utter%20shock%20if%20the%20transportation%20department%2C%20which%20must%20oversee%20the%20railroads%2C%20if%20they%20signed%20off%20on%20that%20deal%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdevelopers-need-trump-sign-off-on-federal-billions-for-nyc-mega-tower-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736848801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67855d718951662c9f1fe405%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdevelopers-need-trump-sign-off-on-federal-billions-for-nyc-mega-tower-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%20entered%20real%20estate's%20big%20leagues%20developing%20this%20NYC%20hotel.%20Developers%20want%20his%20administration's%20help%20to%20tear%20it%20down%20for%20mega-tower.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dgeiger%40businessinsider.com%20(Daniel%20Geiger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdevelopers-need-trump-sign-off-on-federal-billions-for-nyc-mega-tower-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20employee%20told%20me%20he%20was%20quitting%20to%20join%20OpenAI%20in%202016.%20I%20said%20it%20was%20a%20bad%20idea.%20Now%20he's%20an%20AI%20billionaire.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227966%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jack%20Clark%2C%20cofounder%20of%20AI%20startup%20Anthropic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67859af8e294a7514e8cdf25%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225311%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJack%20Clark%2C%20cofounder%20of%20AI%20startup%20Anthropic%3Cp%3EANTHONY%20WALLACE%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C