B%22title%22%3A%22V%20Narayanan%2C%20architect%20of%20India's%20cryogenic%20engine%2C%20takes%20charge%20as%20Isro%20chief%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736845248000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-117231140%2Cimgsize-518474.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fv-narayanan-architect-of-indias-cryogenic-engine-takes-charge-as-isro-chief%2Farticleshow%2F117231174.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22V%20Narayanan%20has%20taken%20over%20as%20the%20new%20secretary%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Space%20and%20chairman%20of%20Isro%2C%20succeeding%20Somanath.%20Known%20for%20his%20pivotal%20role%20in%20India's%20Chandrayaan%20missions%20and%20advancements%20in%20cryogenic%20engine%20technology%2C%20Narayanan%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20is%20expected%20to%20drive%20forthcoming%20missions%2C%20including%20Gaganyaan%20and%20the%20Venus%20Orbiter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fv-narayanan-architect-of-indias-cryogenic-engine-takes-charge-as-isro-chief%2Farticleshow%2F117231174.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20This%20Is%20How%20Much%20Tax%20India's%20Middle%20Class%20Really%20Pays%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20Budget%20Day%20approaches%2C%20the%20debate%20over%20how%20the%20middle%20class%2C%20particularly%20the%20salaried%20class%2C%20bears%20the%20country's%20tax%20burden%20has%20gained%20momentum.%20With%20only%20a%20small%20number%20of%20individual%20taxpayers%20shouldering%20most%20of%20the%20weight%2C%20calls%20for%20much-needed%20relief%20have%20grown%20louder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20tax%20returns%20filed%20by%20individuals%20has%20more%20than%20doubled%2C%20from%203.35%20crore%20in%202013-14%20to%207.54%20crore%20in%202023-24.%20However%2C%20many%20individuals%20file%20zero-tax%20returns%20merely%20for%20compliance%20purposes.%20The%20number%20of%20individuals%20filing%20zero-income%20tax%20returns%20has%20also%20more%20than%20doubled%2C%20from%201.69%20crore%20to%204.73%20crore%20during%20the%20same%20period.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20number%20of%20individuals%20actually%20paying%20income%20taxes%20has%20increased%20from%201.66%20crore%20in%202013-14%20to%202.81%20crore%20in%202023-24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202019%2C%20the%20government%20announced%20a%20reduction%20in%20the%20base%20corporate%20tax%20rate%20for%20existing%20companies%20to%2022%25%20(from%2030%25)%20and%20for%20new%20manufacturing%20firms%20incorporated%20after%20October%201%2C%202019%2C%20to%2015%25%20(from%2025%25).%20Following%20this%20announcement%2C%20corporate%20income%20tax%20(CIT)%20collections%20have%20fallen%20relative%20to%20personal%20income%20tax%20(PIT)%20collections.%20The%20PIT-to-CIT%20ratio%2C%20which%20was%200.7x%20from%202000-10%20to%202019-20%2C%20has%20increased%20to%201.1x%20from%202020-21%20to%202024-25%20(budgeted).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECorporate%20income%20tax%20collections%20have%20grown%20from%20Rs.%205.56%20lakh%20crore%20in%202019-20%20to%20Rs.%2010.2%20lakh%20crore%20in%202024-25%2C%20an%20increase%20of%2083%25.%20During%20the%20same%20period%2C%20personal%20income%20tax%20collection%20grew%20from%20Rs.%204.92%20lakh%20crore%20to%20Rs.%2011.87%20lakh%20crore%2C%20an%20increase%20of%20141%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndividuals%20Contribute%20Generously%20To%20GST%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnnual%20GST%20collections%20in%20India%20range%20from%20Rs.%2018%20lakh%20crore%20to%20Rs.%2020%20lakh%20crore.%20The%20government%20does%20not%20provide%20a%20breakdown%20showing%20the%20respective%20shares%20of%20individuals%20and%20corporations%20in%20this%20pie.%20But%2C%20since%20corporations%20can%20claim%20input%20tax%20credits%20for%20goods%20or%20services%20purchased%20for%20business%20purposes%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20GST%20collections%20are%20accounted%20for%20by%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFive%20states%20account%20for%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20total%20GST%20collections.%20Maharashtra%20holds%20the%20largest%20share%20at%2021.2%25%2C%20followed%20by%20Karnataka%20at%209.3%25%2C%20Gujarat%20at%208.4%25%2C%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20at%208.2%25.%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20ranks%20fifth%2C%20with%20a%20share%20of%206.8%25%20in%202023.%20All%20of%20these%20states%20except%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20have%20urbanisation%20levels%20higher%20than%20the%20national%20average%20of%2031.1%25%2C%20according%20to%20the%202011%20census.%20This%20effectively%20means%20that%20GST%20collections%20are%20higher%20in%20urban%20areas%2C%20where%20India's%20middle%20class%20predominantly%20resides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Extent%20Of%20The%20Actual%20Tax%20Burden%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20examples%20illustrate%20the%20heavy%20burden%20the%20middle%20class%20shoulders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFor%20an%20individual%20who%20earns%20Rs.%2010%20lakh%20and%20saves%2030%25%20(the%20national%20savings%20rate)%2C%20the%20tax%20outgo%2C%C2%A0assuming%20an%20average%20GST%20rate%20of%2015%25%20on%20consumption%2C%20could%20be%20close%20to%20Rs.%201.6%20lakh.%20That%20is%2016%25%20of%20the%20total%20income.%20If%20the%20same%20person%20saves%2015%25%20of%20their%20income%2C%20the%20outgo%20would%20be%2018%25%2C%20and%2020%25%20if%20there%20is%20no%20saving%20at%20all.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20an%20individual%20earns%20Rs.%2020%20lakh%20in%20income%20and%20saves%2030%25%2C%20assuming%20an%20average%20GST%20rate%20on%20their%20expenditure%20of%2018%25%2C%20he%20will%20pay%20Rs.%203.1%20lakh%20in%20income%20tax%20under%20the%20new%20tax%20regime%20and%20Rs.%202%20lakh%20in%20GST%20on%20consumption%20expenditure.%20The%20total%20tax%20paid%20would%20be%20Rs.%205.1%20lakh%2C%20or%2025%25%20of%20the%20income.%20If%20this%20person%20saves%2015%25%2C%20the%20total%20tax%20burden%20would%20come%20to%20around%20%C2%A028%25%2C%20and%2C%20in%20case%20of%20no%20savings%2C%20it%20will%20be%20closer%20to%2031%25.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAssuming%20an%20individual%20earns%20Rs.%201%20crore%20and%20saves%2030%25%2C%20then%2C%20with%20an%20average%20GST%20rate%20of%2023%25%20on%20consumption%20expenditure%2C%20the%20tax%20burden%2C%20both%20direct%20and%20indirect%2C%C2%A0will%20be%20nearly%20Rs%2040%20lakh%2C%20or%2040%25%20of%20the%20income.%20If%20the%20same%20person%20saves%2015%25%2C%20the%20tax%20incidence%20will%20go%20up%20to%2043%25%2C%20and%2C%20in%20case%20of%20no%20savings%2C%20the%20burden%20will%20shoot%20up%20to%2047%25.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20middle%20class%20has%20long%20been%20treated%20as%20a%20cash%20cow%20by%20successive%20governments%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20growing%20demand%20for%20fair%20treatment%2C%20including%20tax%20breaks%2C%20incentives%20for%20vehicle%20and%20home%20purchases%2C%20and%20parity%20with%20corporations%20in%20terms%20of%20deductions.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20household%20savings%20are%20at%20their%20lowest%20and%20wage%20increases%20by%20corporations%20are%20insufficient%20to%20cover%20inflation%2C%20some%20relief%20is%20warranted%20for%20the%20middle%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Amitabh%20Tiwari%20is%20a%20political%20strategist%20and%20commentator.%20In%20his%20earlier%20avatar%2C%20he%20was%20a%20corporate%20and%20investment%20banker.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736845140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-12%2Fnew-500-notes-cash-currency-pti_650x400_81482072336.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-much-tax-does-indias-middle-class-really-pay-7470454%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20middle%20class%20has%20long%20been%20treated%20as%20a%20cash%20cow%20by%20